sative case of quoius in its original use as a possessive adjective like meus. The original genitive of qui and quis was quois (see on eius, 93), and the classical use of quoius (later cuius) is due to a contamina— tion of the possessive adjective and the original genitive. The adjective use of quoius (cuius) is frequent in early Latin and appears occasionally in the later colloquial language.

765. vostri is the genitive of the possessive.
